# Budget Pet — Project Context (V2)

## Stack

| Layer | Tech |
|-------|------|
| Backend | Python 3.11, FastAPI, Uvicorn |
| Frontend | Next.js 15, React 19, TypeScript 5, Tailwind CSS 4, TanStack Query |
| Bot | python-telegram-bot 22 (adapts to V2 in a separate PR) |
| DB | PostgreSQL on Railway (`asyncpg` only — psycopg2 removed in V2) |
| Hosting | Railway (3 services: FastAPI, Next.js, telegram bot) |

## Key Conventions

- **Single DB driver** — only `asyncpg` via `web/db.py` pool singleton. Never use psycopg2.
- **Auth** — Persistent DB-backed sessions (`users`, `sessions` tables). All routes under `/api/*` protected by `AuthMiddleware` (cookie or `Authorization: Bearer`).
- **Plaid as source of truth** — linked accounts, categories, and imported transactions come from Plaid. Offline **cash** spending is recorded as normal `transactions` rows with `source=cash` on the per-user **Cash** wallet account (`GET /api/accounts/cash-wallet`). No legacy manual CSV import.
- **`transactions.source`** — `plaid` | `plaid_sandbox` | `cash` | `manual`. Rows with `plaid_sandbox` are excluded from **reports**, **CSV export**, and **budgets** when `reports_include_plaid_sandbox()` is false; **default is to include** them when `PLAID_ENV=sandbox`, or set `REPORTS_INCLUDE_PLAID_SANDBOX=true` / `false` explicitly (see `web/env_flags.py`).
- **Every new feature** — separate module, not inside large existing files.
- **Docs are source of truth** — always check `docs/` before implementing. Key files: `docs/architecture.md`, `docs/api.md`, `docs/plaid.md`, `docs/data-model.md`.

## Repo Structure

```
budget_pet/
├── web/                  # FastAPI app
│   ├── main.py           # Routers + startup
│   ├── db.py             # asyncpg pool singleton
│   ├── auth/             # Sessions, multi-user
│   ├── accounts/         # Bank/credit/loan/investment accounts
│   ├── transactions/     # Transactions, splits, CSV export
│   ├── categories/       # PFC auto-mapping from Plaid
│   ├── tags/             # User-defined labels (many-to-many)
│   ├── recurring/        # Recurring streams, subscription tracker
│   ├── budgets/          # Budget envelopes by category
│   ├── investments/      # Holdings, securities
│   ├── reports/          # Cash flow, net worth, forecast, health score
│   ├── piggy/            # Savings goals (finance_piggy_banks table)
│   ├── plaid/            # Plaid client, sync repo, scheduler
│   └── migrations/       # v2_init.py — idempotent DDL
├── services/             # Bot adapters (V1, pending V2 migration)
├── frontend/src/         # Next.js (app/, components/, lib/, types/v2.ts)
├── bot.py                # Telegram bot (pending V2 migration)
├── tests/v2/             # pytest — V2 unit tests
└── docs/                 # Current V2 documentation
    └── archive/v1/       # Old V1 docs (for reference only)
```

## Plaid Integration (V2)

- Products: `transactions` + `liabilities` + `investments` + `recurring_transactions`
- All data written to V2 tables: `transactions`, `accounts`, `recurring_streams`, `investment_holdings`
- Category auto-mapping via `personal_finance_category.detailed` (PFC) → `categories` table
- Net worth snapshot taken automatically after each sync
- Sync triggered daily at 03:00 by APScheduler or manually via `POST /api/plaid/sync`
